You are reviewing a code change for a PR. The task was:

LINT01 - Fix react-hooks/exhaustive-deps lint error in MyOrdersDetails/index.tsx:124
The 'enrichedTransaction' conditional could make the dependencies of useMemo Hook (at line 216) change on every render. Wrap the initialization of 'enrichedTransaction' in its own useMemo() Hook.

The change made:

BEFORE (lines 120-135):
```tsx
  const isValidTransactionType = (type: string | undefined): type is TransactionType => {
    return type === 'CREDIT' || type === 'RESCUE' || type === 'EXPIRED' || type === 'REFUNDED';
  };

  const enrichedTransaction = transaction
    ? {
        ...transaction,
        type: isValidTransactionType(passedType) ? passedType : transaction.type,
        icon: passedIcon || transaction.icon,
        status: passedStatus || transaction.status,
        details: {
          ...transaction.details,
          provider: passedOrigination || transaction.details?.provider || '',
        },
      }
    : undefined;
```

AFTER:
```tsx
  const isValidTransactionType = (type: string | undefined): type is TransactionType => {
    return type === 'CREDIT' || type === 'RESCUE' || type === 'EXPIRED' || type === 'REFUNDED';
  };

  const enrichedTransaction = useMemo(() => {
    if (!transaction) return undefined;
    return {
      ...transaction,
      type: isValidTransactionType(passedType) ? passedType : transaction.type,
      icon: passedIcon || transaction.icon,
      status: passedStatus || transaction.status,
      details: {
        ...transaction.details,
        provider: passedOrigination || transaction.details?.provider || '',
      },
    };
  }, [
    transaction,
    passedType,
    passedIcon,
    passedStatus,
    passedOrigination,
  ]);
```

Note: The downstream useMemo that uses enrichedTransaction looks like this:
```tsx
  const processedData = useMemo(() => {
    if (!enrichedTransaction) {
      return {
        cardTitle: '',
        formattedPointsValue: '',
        // ... more fields
      };
    }
    // ... processes enrichedTransaction
  }, [enrichedTransaction]);
```

Focus your review on:
1. Does wrapping enrichedTransaction in useMemo properly fix the chain of dependencies?
2. Will the downstream processedData useMemo now work correctly?

Provide a concise review result.

